<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-39-1321 </DOCNO><TEXT>Reports on a conference held in October 1987 in Moscow during which thedevelopment program of the Soviet coal industry and research programsfor coal coking were discussed. The following problems were evaluated:raw material basis for coking industry, depletion of coking coal andreplacing coal types that cake well with other coal types, methods forcoal mixture treatment prior to coking (heat treatments, selective crushing),formed coke processes, continuous coking, new technologies for air pollutionabatement and control (dry coke quenching with waste heat utilization),investment programs in coking plants. Recommendations for research programsof the major research institutes that specialize in problems of coalcoking were made.</TEXT></DOC>